{"pageProps":{"note":{"id":"5irsjg77tl67tytvpuvff8b","title":"Box","desc":"","updated":1668800580443,"created":1668796776558,"custom":{},"fname":"programing.rust.Smart-Pointer.Box","type":"note","vault":{"fsPath":".","selfContained":true,"name":"docs"},"contentHash":"dde9fe80c0f5783f4f52a2801c9b6e0a","links":[],"anchors":{"box-----point-to-data-on-the-heap":{"type":"header","text":"Box  -  Point to data on the Heap","value":"box-----point-to-data-on-the-heap","line":7,"column":0,"depth":1},"definition--use-cases":{"type":"header","text":"Definition & Use cases","value":"definition--use-cases","line":11,"column":0,"depth":2},"traits":{"type":"header","text":"Traits","value":"traits","line":21,"column":0,"depth":2},"recursive-type":{"type":"header","text":"Recursive type","value":"recursive-type","line":27,"column":0,"depth":2},"the-cons-list":{"type":"header","text":"The cons list","value":"the-cons-list","line":33,"column":0,"depth":3}},"children":[],"parent":"xpd7irdmeinvljufhfbgq6a","data":{}},"body":"<h1 id=\"box\">Box<a aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"anchor-heading icon-link\" href=\"#box\"></a></h1>\n<h1 id=\"box-----point-to-data-on-the-heap\">Box <t> -  Point to data on the Heap</t><a aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"anchor-heading icon-link\" href=\"#box-----point-to-data-on-the-heap\"></a></h1>\n<blockquote>\n<p><a href=\"https://doc.rust-lang.org/book/ch15-01-box.html\">https://doc.rust-lang.org/book/ch15-01-box.html</a></p>\n</blockquote>\n<h2 id=\"definition--use-cases\">Definition &#x26; Use cases<a aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"anchor-heading icon-link\" href=\"#definition--use-cases\"></a></h2>\n<ul>\n<li>Definition: allow user to store data on the heap instead of the stack\n<ul>\n<li>no overhead performance</li>\n<li>doesn't have many extra capabilitites</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n<li>Usecases\n<ul>\n<li>type's size can't be known at <code>compile time</code>, use want to use a value of that type in a context that requires the exact size</li>\n<li>transfer ownership without copying</li>\n<li>own a value that implements <strong>a particular trait</strong> instead of a specific type</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<h2 id=\"traits\">Traits<a aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"anchor-heading icon-link\" href=\"#traits\"></a></h2>\n<ul>\n<li><code>Box&#x3C;T></code> implements\n<ul>\n<li>Deref: treated like a reference</li>\n<li>Drop: clean up </li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<h2 id=\"recursive-type\">Recursive type<a aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"anchor-heading icon-link\" href=\"#recursive-type\"></a></h2>\n<ul>\n<li>A type that can have another value of the <strong>same type</strong> as <strong>part of itself</strong>.\n<ul>\n<li>problem: the compiler needs to know how much space a type takes up</li>\n<li>solution: using box (boxes have a known size)</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<h3 id=\"the-cons-list\">The cons list<a aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"anchor-heading icon-link\" href=\"#the-cons-list\"></a></h3>\n<ul>\n<li>\n<p>The cons list (cons = construct function)</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p>Example: <code>(1, (2, (3, Nil)))</code></p>\n<ul>\n<li>1 pair: value + next pair  </li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p>Computing the Size of a <strong>Non-Recursive Type</strong></p>\n<ul>\n<li>Space of a value = largest variants</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p><code>Box&#x3C;T></code> is a pointer</p>\n<ul>\n<li>\n<p>Has a fixed space (only the pointer is located on the Stack)</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<pre class=\"language-rust\"><code class=\"language-rust\">  <span class=\"token comment\">// example of using Box to create a recursive type </span>\n  <span class=\"token keyword\">enum</span> <span class=\"token type-definition class-name\">List</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span>\n      <span class=\"token class-name\">Cons</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token keyword\">i32</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span> <span class=\"token class-name\">Box</span><span class=\"token operator\">&#x3C;</span><span class=\"token class-name\">List</span><span class=\"token operator\">></span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span>\n      <span class=\"token class-name\">Nil</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span>\n  <span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span>\n\n  <span class=\"token keyword\">use</span> <span class=\"token keyword\">crate</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">::</span><span class=\"token class-name\">List</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">::</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span><span class=\"token class-name\">Cons</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span> <span class=\"token class-name\">Nil</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>\n\n  <span class=\"token keyword\">fn</span> <span class=\"token function-definition function\">main</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">{</span>\n      <span class=\"token keyword\">let</span> list <span class=\"token operator\">=</span> <span class=\"token class-name\">Cons</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token number\">1</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span> <span class=\"token class-name\">Box</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">::</span><span class=\"token function\">new</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token class-name\">Cons</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token number\">2</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span> <span class=\"token class-name\">Box</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">::</span><span class=\"token function\">new</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token class-name\">Cons</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token number\">3</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span> <span class=\"token class-name\">Box</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">::</span><span class=\"token function\">new</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token class-name\">Nil</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>\n  <span class=\"token punctuation\">}</span>\n</code></pre>\n</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n</ul>","noteIndex":{"id":"xfkxbponh0sohobo6pual15","title":"Root","desc":"","updated":1668137379975,"created":1663481872547,"custom":{"nav_order":0,"permalink":"/"},"fname":"root","type":"note","vault":{"fsPath":".","selfContained":true,"name":"docs"},"contentHash":"cb44915142ec96bef8f764f3dc90389e","links":[],"anchors":{"welcome-to-my-page":{"type":"header","text":"Welcome to my page","value":"welcome-to-my-page","line":7,"column":0,"depth":1},"contacts":{"type":"header","text":"Contacts","value":"contacts","line":12,"column":0,"depth":2},"dendron":{"type":"header","text":"Dendron","value":"dendron","line":18,"column":0,"depth":2}},"children":["u5a2e2vvfn3x7k0shuvmb1b","qw8y69zxn8wr7tzz4gtcrrv","q7qw45jglqwmynary64q67c","6wjqcjgkrpeqtmzb1o8o1q8","3ervbn5we7t8v2l2vwtx847","4qi2z0z9fquupbd651xausx","sencgim78q74o1zuyvy1vz7","ue4oml1si982t3mmbthyxi9","zrogwjgtze8ne5joqpz8ty9","oesia0lbzh03fsoy124ck0k","el3p9zjue6h3b6zsl9oejkt","t5grkmcwvu4nl43igsj4gxz"],"parent":null,"data":{},"body":"# Welcome to my page\n\n- This is a place where I write my knowledge in both Vietnamese and English.\n- Please feel free to correct me if there is anything not right.\n\n## Contacts\n\n- [Github](https://github.com/thanhpp)\n- [Discord](https://discord.gg/ugNRjFNqjp)\n- [LinkedIn](https://www.linkedin.com/in/thanhpp/)\n\n## Dendron\n\n- [Home Page](https://wiki.dendron.so/)"},"collectionChildren":null,"customHeadContent":null,"config":{"version":5,"dev":{"enablePreviewV2":true,"enableSelf